4 Configuration
***************

The package installs the following configuration files:

‘/etc/clamdscan-tools/clamdscan-tools.conf’
     Main configuration file with default targets, runtime directories
     and optional integrations.  When the configured runtime directories
     are not writable for a non-root user, the tool automatically falls
     back to ‘$XDG_STATE_HOME/clamdscan-tools/’ (or
     ‘~/.local/state/clamdscan-tools/’) and
     ‘$XDG_DATA_HOME/clamdscan-tools/’ (or
     ‘~/.local/share/clamdscan-tools/’).

‘/etc/clamdscan-tools/excludes.conf’
     Directory-name exclusions such as ‘.git’, ‘node_modules’ or cache
     folders.

‘/etc/clamdscan-tools/prune-paths.conf’
     Absolute paths to skip entirely, for example ‘/proc’ or ‘/sys’.


