5 Runtime Files
***************

During execution, clamdscan-tools stores data in standard locations.  As
root, these are the default system paths:

‘/var/log/clamdscan-tools/’
     Scan logs shown by ‘clamdscan-watch’.

‘/var/lib/clamdscan-tools/state/’
     State files used for resume, generated file lists and auxiliary
     logs.

‘/var/lib/clamdscan-tools/infected/’
     Destination directory for quarantined files when the scan runs with
     sufficient privileges.

   For unprivileged runs where those system paths are not writable,
runtime files are stored in:

‘~/.local/state/clamdscan-tools/log/’
     Per-user scan logs.

‘~/.local/state/clamdscan-tools/state/’
     Per-user state files, file lists and ‘find’ error logs.

‘~/.local/share/clamdscan-tools/infected/’
     Per-user quarantine directory.

   For command-specific usage, see ‘info clamdscan-tools’, ‘man
clamdscan-progress’ and ‘man clamdscan-watch’.



